# Netlify security headers. Netlify serves files in public/ at the site root, so
# this file ships as-is. Applies to every route of the SPA.
#
# CSP NOTES (a wrong CSP white-screens the app — read before editing):
#  - script-src 'self': Vite's production build emits EXTERNAL bundled scripts
#    (no inline JS), so no 'unsafe-inline' is needed for scripts.
#  - style-src 'unsafe-inline': the app uses inline style={} attributes (and
#    Tailwind), which require it. This is the one unavoidable relaxation.
#  - connect-src: Supabase REST + Realtime (wss). Wildcard *.supabase.co works for
#    BOTH PropNest's and Trevis's projects, so no edit needed when we repoint.
#  - Sentry: the *.ingest.*.sentry.io entries cover the US region DSN. If your
#    Sentry project is in the EU, add https://*.ingest.de.sentry.io.
#
# FIRST DEPLOY: ship a Netlify deploy preview, open the console, and confirm there
# are NO "Content Security Policy" violations. If something is blocked, temporarily
# rename the header to "Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only" (reports without
# blocking), fix the directive, then switch back.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://*.supabase.co wss://*.supabase.co https://*.ingest.sentry.io https://*.ingest.us.sentry.io; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; object-src 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
